    <item>
      <title>Making Memories SLICE Think Pink Design Card</title>
      <link>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/think-pink/</link>
      <comments>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/think-pink/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 16 Oct 2009 13:05:35 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.diecutfun.com/?page_id=264</guid>
      <description>The Think Pink Design Card is included with the limited edition pink Making Memories SLICE, or it can also be purchased separately.  For those who do not yet have one of these die cut machines, the limited edition pink model is the way to go because it includes this cartridge (as well as Basic Shapes [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/making-memories-slice/Making_Memories_SLICE-Making_Memories_SLICE_Think_Pink_Design_Card.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The <strong>Think Pink Design Card</strong> is included with the limited edition pink Making Memories SLICE, or it can also be purchased separately.  For those who do not yet have one of these die cut machines, the limited edition pink model is the way to go because it includes this cartridge (as well as Basic Shapes 1).  As a special bonus, a portion of the proceeds from the sale of each one of these machines goes to help in the race to find a cure for breast cancer.</p>
<p>Think Pink is one of the new MS+ Design Cards.  The "M" stands for mirroring, which allows crafters to flip and cut any of the images on the cartridge.  The "S" stands for shadowing, creating layered shadows of any of the die cut shapes.  Finally, the "+" stands for a speed boost update, installing an update on your digital design cutter to speed up the cutting process.</p>
<p>The die cuts on this design card are both feminine and pretty.  Even the font, which includes upper and lower case letters, numbers, and symbols, has an air of femininity to it.  Words and phrases on this cartridge reflect its pink theme of breast cancer awareness, and include triumph, survivor, love, pink, breast cancer, family, walk, race, mother, daughter, sister, Grandma, cure, therapy, experience, life, hope, strong, faith, and friends.</p>
<p>Shapes on this cartridge include silhouettes of women in a variety of poses, as well as shoes, flowers, leaves, scrolls, flourishes, frames and photo corners.</p>
<p>For anyone who knows someone who has battled breast cancer, or is interested in this cause, the <a href="http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/">Think Pink Design Card</a> is the perfect addition to their die cutting library.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-274" style="border: 1px solid black;" title="Slice Think Pink Design Card" src="http://www.diecutfun.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/slice-think-pink-design-card.gif" alt="Slice Think Pink Design Card" width="300" height="300" /></p>
<p>Return to our home page to find out more about the <a href="http://www.diecutfun.com/">Making Memories SLICE</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/think-pink/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
