    <item>
      <title>Making Memories SLICE Studio Essentials Design Card</title>
      <link>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/studio-essentials/</link>
      <comments>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/studio-essentials/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 12 Oct 2009 14:22:14 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.diecutfun.com/?page_id=257</guid>
      <description>The Studio Essentials Design Card for the Making Memories SLICE is a must-have for people who love to scrapbook, and especially for those who enjoy adding journaling to their layouts.  With the ability to cut a wide variety of tags, frames, and labels, this design card is perfect for adding journaling spots to layouts showcasing [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/making-memories-slice/Making_Memories_SLICE-Making_Memories_SLICE_Studio_Essentials_Design_Card.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The <strong>Studio Essentials Design Card</strong> for the Making Memories SLICE is a must-have for people who love to scrapbook, and especially for those who enjoy adding journaling to their layouts.  With the ability to cut a wide variety of tags, frames, and labels, this design card is perfect for adding journaling spots to layouts showcasing pictures of special people, occasions, and memories.  It also gives scrapbookers the ability to cut a wide range of frames and photo corners for their projects.</p>
<p>This design card, which was released in July 2009, also includes a serif font, with upper and lowercase letters, numbers, and typographical and mathematical symbols.  When used with the handheld Making Memories Slice, it can make die cuts ranging in size from one to four inches, in half inch increments, and can be used to cut through cardstock, vellum, vinyl, and photos.</p>
<p>See the picture below which shows the types of cutouts that can be made with the <a href="http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/">Studio Essentials Design Card</a>...</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-260" style="border: 1px solid black;" title="Slice Studio Essentials Design Card" src="http://www.diecutfun.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/slice-studio-essentials-design-card.gif" alt="Slice Studio Essentials Design Card" width="300" height="300" /></p>
<p>&lt;&lt;&lt;To find out more about the <a href="http://www.diecutfun.com/">Slice from Making Memories</a>, return to our home page here at Die Cut Fun.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/studio-essentials/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
