    <item>
      <title>Making Memories SLICE Spellbound Design Card</title>
      <link>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/spellbound/</link>
      <comments>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/spellbound/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 30 Jul 2009 19:32:27 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.diecutfun.com/?page_id=240</guid>
      <description>There's something that's irresistible about Halloween, and perhaps that why the Making Memories SLICE Spellbound Design Card is a favorite.  October 31st always provides ample picture-taking opportunities, and when it comes time to put the photographs of your favorite ghouls and goblins in your scrapbook album, this is one cartridge that you don't want to [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/making-memories-slice/Making_Memories_SLICE-Making_Memories_SLICE_Spellbound_Design_Card.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There's something that's irresistible about Halloween, and perhaps that why the <strong>Making Memories SLICE Spellbound Design Card</strong> is a favorite.  October 31st always provides ample picture-taking opportunities, and when it comes time to put the photographs of your favorite ghouls and goblins in your scrapbook album, this is one cartridge that you don't want to be without!  It's also great for making custom invitations, party favors, and treat bags for all of your "ghoulish" guests.</p>
<p>So, what's included on this "spooktacular" design card?  First, there's a font set, with upper and lowercase letters and numbers.  Of course, it's not just any font set.  No, it's creepy-looking - something Dracula would be proud of!  For each letter, there's three different ways that you can cut it out, providing for lots of mixing and matching.</p>
<p>There are also lots and lots of pumpkins, from traditional pumpkin patch shapes to grinning (and grimacing!) jack o' lanterns.  Ghosts, spiders, creepy eyes, black cats, haunted houses, ravens and bats, skeletons, witches hats and Halloween candy, and even gravestone markers are included on the Making Memories Spellbound cartridge.  If you love Halloween, there's no doubt about it - you will love this design card!</p>
<p>The <a href="http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/">Making Memories SLICE Spellbound Design Card</a> will make die cuts ranging in size from one to four inches.  It will cut die cuts from a variety of materials - so have fun with it.  Cut ghosts shapes from murky white vellum, or use it to cut vinyl pumpkins to decorate your windows.  You are limited by only your imagination!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241" style="border: 1px solid black;" title="Making Memories Slice Spellbound Design Card" src="http://www.diecutfun.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/slice-spellbound-design-card.gif" alt="Making Memories Slice Spellbound Design Card" width="300" height="300" /></p>
<p>&lt;&lt;&lt; Want to learn more about the <a href="http://www.diecutfun.com/">Making Memories SLICE</a>?  Our home page is a good place to start...</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.diecutfun.com/slice-design-cards/spellbound/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
